class Solution {
    public int singleNumber(int[] nums) {
        int xor=0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            xor=xor^nums[i];
        }
        return xor;
    }
}

A hash array only works efficiently when the values are small and non-negative; large values waste a lot of memory and negative values cannot be used as indices directly.

For the Single Number problem, the XOR approach is better because it uses O(1) space and works for all integer values, including negatives.
